    "what_description": "Arnica montana is a perennial plant with yellow flowers, 3-5 cm in diameter, having 12-20 petals, and arranged in dense, terminal clusters. It belongs to the family Asteraceae, and its stem is 20-80 cm tall, hairy, and branched. The leaves are lance-shaped, 5-15 cm long, and 1-3 cm wide, with serrated margins, and are arranged oppositely on the stem. The plant's rhizome contains sesquiterpene lactones, including arnicin and arnicolide, which are responsible for its pharmacological properties. Arnica montana is native to the alpine and subalpine regions of Europe, North America, and Asia.",
