    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Arnica montana are its anti-inflammatory effects, which are attributed to the presence of flavonoids and sesquiterpene lactones that inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and mediators. This plant also exhibits antioxidant properties, protecting cells from oxidative damage by scavenging free radicals, thereby preventing cell death and tissue damage. Additionally, Arnica montana has analgesic properties, providing relief from pain through the inhibition of pain receptors and the release of pain-relieving chemicals such as acetylcholine. The antimicrobial properties of Arnica montana are attributed to the presence of saponins and phenolic acids that disrupt microbial membranes and prevent the growth of pathogens. Its antiseptic properties, due to the presence of volatile oils and phenolic acids, help to prevent infection by inhibiting the growth of bacteria and other microorganisms on wounds.",
