    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Arnica montana are its sesquiterpene lactones, primarily responsible for its anti-inflammatory and antiseptic properties, with compounds like helenalin and dihydrohelenalin exhibiting significant efficacy. Flavonoids, such as kaempferol and quercetin, contribute to the plant's antioxidant activity and potential anti-inflammatory effects. Triterpene saponins, like oleanolic acid and ursolic acid, exhibit anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory properties, while coumarins, including scopoletin and scoparone, may possess anticoagulant and antioxidant activities. These constituents work synergistically to provide the plant's healing effects, including wound healing, anti-inflammatory action, and potential antimicrobial properties. The combined action of these constituents may contribute to the plant's efficacy in treating various conditions, including wounds, bruises, and inflammatory disorders.",
